\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. P. globulifera} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 1100 (1753). Caespitose or creeping,with internodes up to 4 cm. Leaves usually at least 5 cm, 1 mm wide. Sporocarps 4-chambered, c. 3 mm in diameter, erect, subsessile; megaspores ovoid, constricted above the middle, 15-20 in each chamber.{\i  Shallow water, marshy ground, pools and lake margins. • W. Europe, northwards to} 61°{\i  N., extending very locally eastwards to Finland, Poland, Czechoslovakia and S.E. Italy.} Be Br Cz Da Fe Ga Ge Hb He Ho Hs It Ju Lu No Po Rs(?C, E) Su.
