\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 24.    SALVINIACEAE}
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  Edit. †D.H. Valentine & D.M. Moore.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Stems slender, branched, floating. Leaves in whorls of 3, very hairy; 2 of the leaves entire, floating, the third submerged. Heterosporous; sori at the base of the submerged leaves, stalked, surrounded by a thin-walled, hairy indusium, and consisting of either numerous microsporangia or a few megasporangia, or occasionally mixed.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 1.               Salvinia}                  Séguier 
\par   

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By A. Lawalrée.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Aquatic plants. Floating leaves covered with stellate hairs; submerged leaves finely divided and root-like. Microsporangia producing 64 microspores; megasporangia with 1 megaspore; prothalli developing inside the floating spores.
\par

